            {
              "date": "2026-03-09",
              "subject": "Week of March 9-13 Newsletter & BEST Writing Prep",
              "summary": "Last newsletter before Spring Break covered the week of March 9-13. Key highlights: All work was due Thursday March 13 \u2014 check Canvas and Skyward for any missing assignments. Field Day was held March 12. Spring Break runs March 14-22. School resumes March 23 with the 4th Grading Period. The BEST Writing Assessment is March 31 (120-min computer-based state test). Blooket review links were shared for Math (Extend Thinking Numbers to 1000), Science (Human Body Parts), and Social Studies."
            },
            {
              "date": "2026-03-11",
              "subject": "BEST Writing Assessment Preparation",
              "summary": "Reminder about the 4th Grade BEST Writing Assessment on Tuesday, March 31. This is a 120-minute computer-based state test. Students should get good sleep, eat a healthy breakfast, and avoid electronics the night before. No personal electronics allowed during testing."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "kidId": "kaia",
          "teacher": "Ms. Smith",
          "messages": [
            {
              "date": "2026-03-08",
              "subject": "Week of March 9-13 Newsletter",
              "summary": "Last newsletter before Spring Break. Phonics focus: Diphthongs (ou, ow, oi, oy, au, aw). ELA: Assessing similes, idioms, alliteration, rhyme schemes & themes in poems; context clues and word relationships. Math: Compare Numbers Using Place Value. Science: Human body parts and basic functions. Social Studies: Native American Cultures quiz. Assessments scheduled throughout the week. Homework: Math pages 467-468 (Mon), 469-470 (Tue), Performance Task pages 475-476 (Wed). Wednesdays are School Spirit days."
            },
            {
              "date": "2026-03-08",
              "subject": "Blooket Review Games Shared",
              "summary": "Ms. Smith shared Blooket review links for students to practice at home: Math (Numbers to 1000), Science (Human Body Parts), and Social Studies review game. Poetry vocabulary was also shared (poem, line, stanza, break, poet). These are great for review during Spring Break."
            }
          ]
        }
